cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.AI, cs.IT 

This paper deals with the problem of computing approximate Nash equilibria in bimatrix games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The focus is on algorithms with low communication complexity, which involves the study of data structures (cs.DS) and communication protocols (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of approximation algorithms (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT) in achieving the desired results.
